						               													<description>Break the Bank is a trivia game where players answer questions for money.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are five categories of questions: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Story Land&amp;#10;    Geography&amp;#10;    Sports]&amp;#10;    Show Biz/Music&amp;#10;    History&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player spins for a question category and if the question is answered correctly, gains money, then advances towards the &amp;quot;Gateway to the Bank&amp;quot;.  Once the &amp;quot;Gateway&amp;quot; has been reached, a special Bank Breaker question is asked, and if answered correctly, the player gains one of twelve $100,000 bonus coins and returns to start again at the beginning of the track.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Penalties are applied for answering a question wrong.  These range from losing money to moving backwards on the track. Play continues until all of the bonus coins are awarded.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player with the most money wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;An interesting note:  each question card contains two questions, one marked 'grown-up' and one marked 'youngster'.  These can be used to balance the game if younger players are involved or handicap players if the 'yougster' questions are considered too easy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A nice trivia game, but limited to only 30 questions per category.  And because the game was produced in the 50s, the questions (which were current at the time) are dated.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
